## Block 13 — Inner-CV Loop: Calibration & Threshold Tuning

After selecting the best KAN per fold (by validation AUC across K1–K4):

### Calibration

- Carve out the **last 20% of the training fold** as a calibration set.
  This is the same val_inner used for early stopping, but calibration is
  fitted AFTER training is complete.
  **The test fold is never used for calibration.**
- Call `trainer.calibrate(X_val_inner.values, y_val_inner.values)`.
- This fits an isotonic regression mapping raw sigmoid outputs to calibrated
  probabilities.

### Threshold Tuning

- Grid search thresholds from 0.30 to 0.70 in steps of 0.01.
- Evaluate F1 on `X_val_inner` (the calibration partition of training data).
- Select the threshold with the highest validation F1.
- Apply this threshold unchanged to the test fold.
  **Never tune the threshold on test data.**

### Final Test Evaluation

- Get calibrated probabilities on test fold:
  `calibrated_test_probs = trainer.predict_proba(X_test.values)[:, 1]`
- Apply the tuned threshold to get hard predictions.
- Compute final metrics: AUC, F1, Brier, log-loss, accuracy.
- Compute the annualized Sharpe ratio of a strategy that goes
  long when prediction=1 and short when prediction=0, using daily
  log returns from `bins.loc[test_labeled, 'ret']`.
- Log everything to `trial_registry`.

**End of the inner-CV for-loop.** Close the loop here.

